title: Medline Remedy Olivamine Antifungal Cream 4 oz. QTY: 1
reviewText: I purchased this because it had some good reviews scattered among the not so good so I decided to give it the benefit of the doubt. My purpose for the purchase was to control jock itch. I had been using Lotrimin, a product of Japan, which worked very well but is a bit pricey. I also tried Clotrimozole, a product of Korea, which was a cheapo Lotrimin wannabe that worked but did not work well enough to renew. I decided to give Medline a shot since pricewise it was between the other two that I had mentioned (an add on item that requires a $25.00 purchase). Medline is a product from some secret location that Medline is ashamed to reveal. My guess would be China since lately I have noticed a trend in hiding the source of products from China.I took a shower, dried thoroughly as instructed and removed the Medline cap from the tube. Wow! I was overwhelmed with an odor bad enough to be classified as putrid. After waiting a while to let my nostrils become indoctrinated with this foul stench I put a layer of this greasy  substance on my itchy area and waited for the results. The reason I applied this product is because I did not think it would be fair to write a review on the stench alone without actually using the product.There was no immediate relief as was the case with Lotrimin but after a few hours there was a detectable reduction of the severity of the itch. However, after leaving this grease on all day there never was significant itch relief.  I have tried many jock itch relief products and this is by far the worst. It is no wonder that Medline is ashamed to reveal the manufacturer. Goodbye Medline wherever you are.

title: Zeasorb Antifungal Treatment Powder, Athletes Foot, 2.5oz
reviewText: I am a "mature" individual who has reached portly status. In other words, I am a large old antique. I sweat a lot in the groin area. I used to use baby powder and it worked somewhat but then I decided to try various grease products. They all provided a fair amount of relief for the persistent jock itch. Problem with grease is that sometimes you get a compelling urge to just reach on down and give the itch a scratch with the old faithful finger nail. When you reach down there and hit the grease and sweat it is a bit icky. That is the advantage of powder.When I used baby powder it required a substantial amount of powder to get the job done. This resulted in powder falling around in other unwanted areas. Zeasorb came to the rescue. It takes just a light layer of Zeasorb powder sprinkled over the sweaty crotch to get the skin dried up in a hurry. Along with drying the crotch area the primary benefit is the reduction and/or elimination of the jock itch. This product is far better than baby powder and if you are compelled to reach down and scratch it feels better than grease.I am not knocking grease because at times I still use grease and sometimes I use powder. Depends on the occasion.

title: Remington Products Xr1350 Hyper Series Rotary Shaver
reviewText: It has been my experience that most of the items I purchase that are made in China are not very good. This is an exception. I recently purchased a Braun and a 4-pack of cartridges for over $200.00. This Remington is every bit as good as the Braun if not better. I was skeptical at first because of the unimpressive charger and the instruction sheet that directs you to certain numbered pages that are not numbered. However, when I picked up the shaver to slide it into the charger the feel of the shaver was quite good.After charging initially for 24 hours as instructed I read the section on shaving which stated that optimal results are obtained with a gel. So, I shaved one side of my face without the gel. Next, I climbed into the shower, wet my face and applied gel to the unshaved side of my face. I rinsed my face and felt both sides of my face. The side which had the gel was clearly the winner. Not only was the shave better but my face on the side without the gel felt as if it was rubbed or slightly scratched while the gelled side felt natural.This is a really nice shaver when used with gel but I did have to deduct one star for the following reasons:- Cleaning the head of the shaver is a somewhat of a tricky process (although I admit it is better than the expensive Braun  cartridges).- The trimmer is mediocre and does not have a way to lock it in place when using.- If you are gonna say to go to a certain page number then number the page. (Yeah, I know this is kinda picky).- It is made in China instead of the USA where we desperately need jobs.

title: Dr. Scholl's Odor Destroyer Deodorant Spray 4.7 oz.
reviewText: I was ordering some foot powder and I asked my wife if she wanted to add something to the order. I am not dumb enough to ask her if she wanted foot deodorant but just if she wanted anything. To my surprise she said she has been using Dr. Scholl's Odor Destroyer Spray for many years and that she could use a refill. OK, so I am not very observant when it comes to my wife's feet.She said she uses this deodorant mostly in the cold season when she wears socks and shoes. It removes any odor and helps with moisture. She does not need it in the summer if she is wearing sandals. She said she loves this product and the cost locally is around 6 or 7 bucks per 4.7 ounces. The cost is similar to that at Amazon but adding it to my order means she does not have to go to a store which saves her time and gas money. By adding it to my order it is all good.If she says it is a good product then by golly it is a good product. She recommends it highly.

title: Dr. King's Natural Medicine Regional Allergies, Hawaii U.S, 2 Fluid Ounce
reviewText: This crazy weather we have been having has caused symptoms including itchy, watery eyes, runny nose, sneezing, sore throat,  cough, stuffy nose, fatigue, itchy, irritated skin, and headache. Versions of this product are associated with different parts of the USA. However, I could not find one targeted for the southeastern part of the country. I figured that the closest I could come would be the Hawaii version. So, I figured it would be worth a try.I did not expect to get help for all the symptoms that I was experiencing but I hoped that at least if some of the problems, especially the watery eyes and/or the coughing would be helped and then it would be a job well done. I followed the directions regarding the dosage and had no reaction whatsoever. Not only was there no help for the watery eyes and coughing but for anything else as well. Nothing. Nada. Zippo.Normally I would give a product that does not work just one star. But, to be fair, I do not live in Hawaii. I live in Georgia, home of the UGA Dawgs who will be the NCAA national champions this year in football. Hopefully, when the warm weather finally kicks in most of my problems will disappear.There is a review of this product that has been posted by Hawaii residents so although my review may not be helpful to anyone living outside of Georgia you can get a Hawaii on-site review from folks who actually live there.

title: Panasonic ES-LT71-S Arc3 Men's Electric Shaver Wet/Dry with Flexible Pivoting Head and Automatic Cleaning System
reviewText: I have tried many electric shavers and have had many different results. The power cord for my last shaver got accidentally thrown out so I decided to go back to the Gillette and  forget about electric versions. However, Amazon had this Panasonic on a heck of a deal and I could not resist.I plugged the power cord directly into the shaver and let it charge. I took a shower and then gave this shaver a try. I was really surprised at the results because most instructions say you have to use a shaver for a month or so for the shaver to become acquainted with your beard. Not in this case because this shaver quickly introduced itself to my beard and then proceeded to remove it quickly and smoothly. But as surprised as I was with this performance the best was yet to come.Of the dozen or more electric shavers I have owned I never had one that would cut the hair just under my nostrils .I  always had to use one of those little nose hair things to finish the job. To my utter amazement this Panasonic gave me a complete shave including the area up close to the nostril area. I would give this more stars if it were possible. Best electric shaver  have ever owned.

reviewText: When I stand in the shower I get a pain in my lower back so I wanted to give this a try. When it arrived there were six chair parts plus one of the best instruction sheets I have seen in a long time. The chair parts consisted of 4 legs, a seat and a back. No tools were required to assemble the chair. The legs simply slide into place very easily. The legs have a soft rubber tip which keeps the chair from sliding in the tub. The rubber tips also prevent damage to the tub (or shower). All four legs are adjustable. The back slides onto the seat and provides the support that keeps my back from going south. The seat is wide enough to handle a posterior of ample size.This chair fits into my tub perfectly and makes taking a shower a pleasure instead of a painful task. This is a quality product by Moen, a company from which I have other quality products. If you are in the market for a shower chair I strongly recommend this one. It is a winner.

title: Lotrimin Ultra Cream, 30 Gram
reviewText: One of life's biggest nuisances is jock itch. I have tried many brands and many types of creams and powders with some being helpful and some being totally worthless. Although this is hyped as being for athlete's foot between the toes I noticed that a reviewer wrote that it helped in the groin area so I decided to give it a shot. When I received this the back of the container did say that it cured most jock itch.The way I used this product was after taking a morning shower, drying thoroughly then applying a coat of this Lotrimin. I could  feel the benefits almost immediately. This is an expensive product coming in at around 14 bucks for just a tad over an ounce. But, as the old saying goes "You get what you pay for" and I paid for jock itch relief and that is what I got. Good product. Worth a try if you have jock itch. I can't speak for athlete's foot because I don't have that problem but for jock itch it is a big help

I also sometimes buy a similar product at BJs for a cost of $29.99 for 132 chewable tablets. It still provides Max the boost he needs but it also gives me some relief from joint pain which I have incurred after getting hit by a pickup truck while taking my daily morning walk. I have had surgery to relieve most of the pain but there is still some residual pain from the accident. This Jarrow helps to ease that pain. At $17.47 for120 capsules it is a price that is hard to beat. I recommend this for you and if you have a dog with hip and joint problems then this will help for that as well.

title: Clotrimazole Anti Fungal Cream Family Care 1% USP
reviewText: This claimed to be comparable with Lotrimin and even copied the Lotrimin colors in the packaging. The carton asks you to compare the active ingredient in Lotrimin with the active ingredient in Clotrimazole. The active ingredient in Lotrimin is Butenafine hydrochloride. The active ingredient in Clotrimazole is Clotrimazole. I tried to set up a chemistry lab to make the comparison but because I am an engineer rather than a chemist I lacked the proper training and equipment  to make the comparison.I had been using Lotrimin which cost me $13.79 for the 1.1 oz tube. When I saw the Clotrimazole claim with the price tag of $0.01 for 1 oz I could not resist making the purchase. A shipping charge of $3.35 was added to my order for a total of$3.36 which was still much less than the Lotrimin.After having used both products I found that I could make a comparison without the necessity of a chemistry lab. Lotrimin relieves my jock itch completely with no side effects. Clotrimazole adds a significant burn to accompany the itch. The major portion of the burn lasts about 1 1/2 hours. After that length of time the burn and the itch are significantly reduced but not ever eliminated. The price is right but I prefer paying a higher cost for the products that leave me pain and itch free.

title: Raspberry Ketones Miracle Fat Burner and 100 % Purest Professional Formula for Natural Weight Loss, 120 Count
reviewText: There has been a lot of hype recently about the phytonutrients found in raspberries. Rheosmin, also knows as raspberry ketones. specifically has become a focus of researchers for its potential in boosting weight loss.  While there are no hard studies proving the weight management theories yet, the early results are promising.It is believed that raspberry ketones might boost enzyme activity, oxygen consumption, and heat production in fat cells, thereby decreasing the risk of growing obesity. It is also believed that raspberry ketones might have a beneficial effect on the pancreas by slowing the activity of fat digesting enzymes. The result may help prevent the absorption of fat.Studies have proven that organically grown fresh raspberries hold superior health and nutritional benefits over non- organic crops. Certainly fresh raspberries would be preferable to a supplement but we do not live in an ideal world. With the cost of fresh organic raspberries above $4.99 per half pint here on the gulf coast, supplements are my only viable option. I am currently evaluating a bottle of Pure Raspberry Ketones from Summit Nutritions and I have been surprised by the positive results so far.It is hard to review a dietary supplement with only a couple of weeks of testing but I can share my results so far. My energy level has noticeably increased. I feel more focused and there actually does seem to be a bit more time in the day. Is this a placebo effect or Pure Raspberry Ketones revving my metabolism? Perhaps it is too soon to tell but for now I am a hopeful believer.

title: #1 PURE Raspberry Ketones,1000 mg Per Serving, 100% Pure All Natural Appetite Control Suppressant Supplements Diet Pills for Men and Women. Dr. Oz Recommended, Lean Organic Ingredients - Great Weight Loss Formula & Benefits - Top Reviews, Lose Weight With 60 Max Double Strength Fat Burner Veg Capsules- Sold EXCLUSIVELY by Pure Body Naturals(TM)
reviewText: This is an interesting product with AMAZING potential. Raspberry Ketone is an organic compound derived from red raspberries. I should say usually derived from red raspberries because the compound can be reproduced in a lab. Let's just say no to items that come from a lab yet are easily obtained in nature. Deal? Ok, Pure Body Naturals Raspberry Ketone supplements are 100% natural and contain no fillers or extras. This is a high quality product and definitely a good place to start if you are interested in seeing what the addition of Raspberry Ketone to your diet can do for you.This chemical extracted from red raspberries has not yet been studies in depth. Preliminary studies in animals show that it seems to increase weight loss by affecting a hormone in the body called adiponectin. Adiponectin is a protein hormone that helps regulate the metabolism in part by modulating glucose levels and fatty acids. One very important fact found by researchers is that the higher the levels of adiponectin the lower the percentage of body fat in adults.Dr. Oz suggests beginning with 100 mg and working up until you see results. This makes sense, of course. It would lessen any side effects and be easier on the tummy. All other research I found, however, does suggest higher doses.  The suggested dosage for optimal weight loss of Raspberry Ketone by Pure Body Naturals is 500 mg taken twice a day. If you are wondering why you can't just eat a lot of raspberries, well, it is not that easy. In order to get 1,000 mg of raspberry ketones from fresh red raspberries you would need to eat 90 pounds. I love raspberries and I love to eat but that just is not possible. Plus, all of the calories and sugar would negate the whole process.I starting taking 500 mg with breakfast and didn’t notice any difference at all. After 3 days I increased my intake adding another 500 mg at dinnertime. That was the key that unlocked my energy gates! I even lost 2 pounds in 11 days. That’s huge for me. Mostly, though, it was the increase in energy that thrilled me. I take a prescription drug to combat chronic fatigue so anything that can help me naturally is a gift. Of course, the raspberry ketone supplement hasn’t replaces my prescription but I have hope that it might assist me in lowering the dose of the pharmaceutical. I did check with my doctor before beginning the supplement and you should too. in fact, always talk to your doctor before adding a new supplement to your diet. Just because a product is 100% natural does not mean it can’t interact with your medications or cause unwanted side effects. After you get the okay from your doc, give Pure Body Naturals Raspberry Ketone supplements a try. You might just be amazed!While I received a free bottle for testing and review all opinions here are my own. I was not obligated to give a positive review and will receive no compensation.

reviewText: Personal care products for men have only recently received serious attention. Ten years ago men that used anything more than hair get were labelled "metrosexual" and it wasn't exactly a compliment. Why were men considered effeminate for  wanting to have healthy skin and hair? I have no idea but I am very glad that time has passed and I'm seeing more and more specialty products for men on the market. My new favorite is Barbershop Shave Soap Bar in a Jar by BebeLush. This artisan soap is made with a variety of specially blended essential oils. It contains no artificial coloring or chemically created fragrances.I have fond memories of watching my grandfather shave when I was a small child. It was quite a production and nothing like the streamlined electric razor quick shave of today. I would sit on the vanity in my grandparent’s pink tiled bathroom and carefully hand him each implement one by one. Except the razor blades that had to be replaced in that stainless steel razor all the time, of course. Papaw handled those himself. But I remember his badger bristle shaving brush and how he used it to whisk the special powder and water into a rich foamy lather. The lather smelled like Mentholatum but still better than the shaving creams that were produced in aerosol cans back then. They say that smell triggers the strongest memories and I think that must be true because Mentholatum gives me the warm fuzzies. Thanks to BebeLush, however, our grandchildren will hopefully get their Papaw shaving memories triggered by the natural scents of Barbershop Shave Soap Bar in a Jar.Barbershop Shave Soap Bar in a Jar is available in two scents; the woodsy Cedarwood, Cassia and Clove, and the crisp zing of Bay Rum, Orange, and Clove. BebeLush uses natural organic ingredients in its products including shea, cocoa and mango butters for their intensely hydrating and luxuriously smoothing properties. Clearly this is not your average shave soap.  Barbershop Shave Soap Bar in a Jar is made for the most discerning of men (or women) in need of a shaving lather that does more than just get the job done.* I received a free sample of this product for testing and review purposes. All opinions expressed here are my own.

reviewText: Checking my weight is as much fun as a root canal. No. Root canals are much more fun. So when I have to weigh myself I want the scale to be completely accurate. When you move it back to a hard surface bring tissues. You will cry. Consider yourself warned.

title: SambaMD Back Relief Wheelchair Cushion, Black
reviewText: The SambaMD™ Back Relief Wheelchair Cushion was designed to make wheelchairs more comfortable. More specifically, it was intended to reduce the pain caused by sitting in a wheelchair – the pain that comes from remaining in the same position for too long. Wheelchair seats don’t normally allow for much movement, if any at all. In fact, they are usually intended for people that have lost their core stability and need assistance remaining upright while in a sitting position. The SambaMD is different. This product is only recommended for wheelchair users that are able to sit upright on their own and is not for those without proper core stability.  The SambaMD encourages the body’s natural need to move. The goal is to avoid inactivity of the core stabilizing muscles and relieve the stiffness, back pain, and muscle fatigue that often accompanies wheelchair use.Researchers have found that pain is not the only result of this inability to move as our bodies were intended. It has been linked to many health issues like cardiovascular disease, cancer and premature death. In my dad’s case it has caused a decline in his equilibrium. The longer he sits the harder it becomes to walk later. Can you imagine the frustration? Luckily, Body Ryzm LifeSciences/Perspectis, Inc. helps alleviate this problem with the SambaMD™ Back Relief Wheelchair Cushion.Here is a bit about the SambaMD™ adjustable skin protection E2622 wheelchair cushion from their web site:Proprietary adjustable air core enables unique 5-in-1 performance.Wheelchair Cushion with memory foam for better pressure distrubutionWheelchair Cushion with customization valve for instant adjustment to ultimate comfortStability Seat for neuromuscular stimulation to revitalize sensitivity of the trunkPosture Wedge for improving sitting posture and reducing back pain and fatigueTailbone Cushion for relieving pressure to tailbone and thighsProstate Seat for relieving pressure to perineal body and protecting coccyx & prostate glandThis cushion relies on air to simulate the normal movements a body would make while sitting. It’s the same basic principle of those hospital beds that are used in long term care units. I can vouch for the relief those beds provide personally! When I read about the SambaMD cushion being filled with puffs of air I knew we had to get this cushion. Body Ryzm LifeSciences kindly provided me with a cushion to review free of charge.If you or a loved one spend any time confined to a wheelchair, I urge you to consider the SambaMD™ Back Relief Wheelchair Cushion. Consult your doctor to see if it might be right for your situation and if it might be covered by your insurance.

title: Coromega Big Squeeze Omega 3, Mango Nectar, 16 Ounce
reviewText: Although the flavor is Mango Nectar, the true behind the scenes flavor is fish.  You can mix this with anything you want, but I just take it straight on a spoon.  I love seafood so the fish taste did not bother me, but it reminded me of eating smoked salmon.  They advertise it does not have a fish or fish after taste, but it does.  I did not get the after burp taste like with some fish oil supplements, but don't believe when they said it does not taste like fish.  You get 45 two teaspoon servings in a pouch.It is advertised as better absorption compared to soft gels but I have no way to tell.  I did not mind the taste and it did not bother my stomach.  It kind of reminds me of pepto bismo in the way the texture feels.  You could probably spread it on a Lox bagel and enjoy it without worrying about the fish taste.I normally do not have problems with Fish Oil and do not mind the taste so depending on which is the better deal in the future is what I would buy.  If you cannot stand taking soft gels, then this is for you.

title: Dove Men + Care Anti-Perspirant Deodorant, Fresh Awake, 2.7 Ounce
reviewText: This goes on smooth and helps me stay dry.  I like the scent as it is not overpowering, and does not affect my cologne.  You have to let it dry a bit before putting on your clothes as you will get deodorant streaks on it if you do not.  I cannot attest to the 48 hour protection as I like to shower daily, but it has been working great every day since I started using it.  I've used Dove deodorants before and they even work great in the Summer when it is 100+ degrees.  However, the sweating results are a bit different.  No deodorant stops sweat from happening in Summer heatwave.I have sensitive dry skin and this does not bother my skin.  I like this product and will purchase it in the future.  I highly recommend it.

title: Speed Stick Gear Body Spray, Fresh Force, 4 Ounce
reviewText: This was an OK deodorant.  The fragrance is light and generic of most spray deodorants.  It was ok for daily use, but not for strenuous activity.  I was out mowing the lawn in 80 degree weather and I was sweating like crazy in the sun.  The one thing I do not like about these type of deodorants is that if you spray in an enclosed space, the fragrance will engulf the room.  My window was closed in the bathroom and the smell just filled up the room.  With normal stick deodorant, I never have that problem.I like this deodorant because it does not leave streaks in my clothes and dries fairly quick when putting on.  I do not like when it touches my skin on a cold chilly morning.  When it becomes really hot here in the east coast, I will use it outdoors when I have a tank top on.  To me, this is meant for more active people who do a lot of outdoor activities.  I recommend this if you are active outdoors and want to constantly apply.

I would start out slow though because introducing too much protein to your diet too fast will give you the runs.  I recommend this.

title: Waterpik WP-660 Aquarius Professional Water Flosser
reviewText: This Water Flosser is a joy to use.  It comes sealed in package so you can use it straight out of the box after you prime it.  All the parts came sealed as well.  The look and size is just right and is smaller than a standard Listerine bottle.  I love the fact there is an actual "on/off" switch for the spray instead of holding down a button.  It is more convenient to have a switch you can slide to temporarily shut off the water.I fill the container near full with filtered water and add some Listerine in and floss with this.  You can use this alone, but I prefer to still use dental floss in combination with this.  It comes with plenty of tips and a tongue scraper.  At the highest setting, it can spray grime off my sink!  I only use it at about the #6 setting.  I tried using the highest setting but my gums could not take it.I feel I get a pretty good clean and feel my gums massaged.  You can also set it to massage and it does a gentle pulse, but I don't really use that feature.This water flosser looks great and works even better.  I highly recommend it.

title: 4X Advanced Eye Health, 120 Count
reviewText: Ever since I got Lasiks, I have been taking Lutein supplements to maintain my vision.  With all supplements, results may vary.  I haven't noticed any difference in my vision, good or bad, but I take it for the insurance.  You get 120 soft gels in this package and it is suggested to take 4 a day.  You do get a good substantial amount of lutein, and some other ingredients per pill.  The pills are easy to swallow and do not upset my stomach.Other Lutein Supplements I take are 1 pill a serving and deliver 2.5mg Lutein per serving, which is comparable to this product.  Taking all 4 delivers 10 mg Lutein a day, but you could take less if you desire.  There is no daily recommended amount to take, but the consensus is 10 mg a day.It's a great value for the amount of supplement you get.  If you want eye health insurance, get yourself some.  I recommend it.

title: Degree Clinical Protection Anti-Perspirant Deodorant for Women, Stress Control, 1.7 Ounce
reviewText: From my wife's perspective:I have been using clinical strength anti-perspirant for a few years. Mostly during the summer and using a regular anti-perspirant during the winter to take a break from the high aluminum in the clinical strength. I've used degree, secret, and dove clinical strength depending on which was on sale or I had a coupon for. Clinical strength deodorant costs more than a regular deodorant.This degree clinical strength anti-perspirant works as well as any other I have tried, if you use it as instructed. It has the same amount (20%) of aluminum as the Dove clinical strength I had last used. The key is to apply it at night as instructed or at least early in the morning hours before you might start sweating. It needs time to absorb into your skin and dry completely. This specific product is supposed to keep you dry even through stress. Some people who do not sweat a lot might not realize that when stressed you do sweat more. I have found that when stressed even clinical strength can lose its effectiveness for me. I haven't had a stressful enough event (good for me) to prove that specific claim made by this anti-perspirant. It also claims the protection can last the next day after a shower. I have not found that to be true. I can say that it will last the next day if you don't shower.What I didn't like was the scent of this deodorant. It smells to me like a pine forest or Irish spring body soap. To me the scent was too masculine. That is just my personal scent preference. I felt like the scent could definitely compete with a perfume.

title: BPI Sports B4 The Once-Daily Fat Burner, 30-Count
reviewText: Like other fat burners now a days, these are basically just caffeine pills.  I do feel I can go longer without eating and do get a pick me up from it, but I can not say my results have improved.  I drink a lot of coffee throughout the day so maybe the caffeine does not work for my system like others, but it will give you the jitters and energy if you are caffeine sensitive.  I do not get any bad side effects unless I wake up and take one first thing in the morning.  When I do that, it makes me want to puke.  I suggest taking one an hour after a small breakfast.Since ephedra is banned, the best kind of fat burners allowed is pretty much caffeine types.  Ephedra worked wonders for me and I lost so much weight with those, even without additional exercise.  However with these, I do not see the same type of results.  This one did not deliver any miracle results for me but results will vary.  If you are new to fat burners, start with lower doses than recommended as they do have a tendency to make you nauseous.

title: MIRA Digital Body Fat Scale & Body Fat Analyzer with 8 User Auto Recognition & Max 400 Lb. Capacity (Blue)
reviewText: This is a very sleek and light scale made by MIRA.  It is very easy to use and program.  It allows for up to 8 different people to use and track their progress.  The scale uses Bio-electrical impedance analysis to determine the levels of fat, bone, and muscle in your body.  You have to stand on it bare feet because it sends a low level electrical signal through your body fat and then measures the resistance it encounters.  It is not recommended for people who have devices like pacemakers or any other implanted medical devices, metal plates/screws or contraceptive appliances (according to MIRA).The display is very bright and text is large and easy to read.  It has a max weight limit of 400 lbs.  I feel the scale is pretty accurate and am now using it to track my progress.  Some people are bigger than others and a simple number does not give you all the facts.  Muscle weighs more than fat so it is always nice to know how healthy you are based on other factors besides one simple number.I'm also using this to weigh my baby.  I stand on it a few times and see if the numbers come back consistent, and then hold my 5 month in my arms to see how much weight he is gaining.It has a smooth surface, almost glass like and wipes down easily.  There is no button to push to turn on and it turns on when you step on it and has an auto off after 10 seconds.I really like this scale and I highly recommend it.*Sample provided by Manufacturer for Review

title: Rutacleanse Natural Acting Detox (Removes Caffeine), 30 Count
reviewText: So I have to get up early 5 days a week to take my daughter to school and then work.  Yeah I know I could use the school bus service but I enjoy getting my child to school safely and making sure she is happy about school and also well enough to be there.  Anyway this means bed at a reasonable time and I have been keeping off the coffee for those 5 days because it disturbs my sleep.This is a hard thing to do, coffee for me is a way of life and one of my few 'bad vices' so not drinking it for 5 days is a test.  Then in comes this product - something that removes caffeine?  Does this mean I can still go into my local McDonald's and inflict the very strong to strong coffee on myself 7 days a week?  I am not joking about this by the way, I don't know why they do it but I need 4 sugars and 4 creamers to make it just right but hey it is cheap, free refills and free wi-fi.  Again now I can still drink coffee?Well I tried this and if you take a capsule a few hours before bed then it seems to do the trick.  Often I sleep then wake but I have noticed I sleep through most nights now.  Not sure why this product works, it is derived from a fruit but they say it detoxes your body so probably why.  I am still not going to go crazy on the caffeine but nice to know there is something to take if I overdo it and surprising it seems to work for me most of the time.

title: Tide Original Scent Liquid Laundry Detergent ,  50 Fl Oz,  2 Count
reviewText: Tide is P&G's strongest detergent. I know because I did marketing for them in the past. This product performs as you would expect it to. Over the years, they have gone from powder to liquid, regular to concentrated ultra, and changed the formula to be more eco-friendly (but with less cleaning power). reviewText: My Testimony: I'm 67 and my knees are bone on bone. I'm at the end of my knee shot therapy. I tried to walk and made it 50 yards from the car and 50 yards back and I was in big time pain. I was hoping for some sort of relief and something that would be easy to take and not cost a fortune. After a week of taking this product as advertised I noticed my knees were feeling a bit better. I went back to the walking track and made the entire lap of 1.2 miles and I barely made the loop. I was slow but I made the loop. My knees were on fire. All I can write is that after another week of taking this product I'll be back at the loop to see what happens. I'm taking the pain but I can see a noticeable difference in the level of pain. A journey of 1,000 miles starts with the first step. It seems to be off to a good start with me and knee replacement is not an option.There it is straight-up. Seems to work right out of the hole and it might get better as I go. Time will tell.

reviewText: My husband had two failed carpel tunnel surgeries, and his right hand is still quite painful, even several years after the second surgery.  The Day Brace helped with the pain immensely.  However, he could wear the Night Brace less than an hour, before the pain required that he remove the brace.  After 15 minutes, his ring and middle finger started tingling. title: Gaia Herbs Herbal Energy Plus Immune Support Nutritional Supplement Bottle, 12 Count
reviewText: Even though this supplement is 99.9 caffeine free, if you are sensitive to caffeine (or herbal stimulants), you may still have a caffeine-like reaction to Gaia Herbal Energy.  I know I did.  Caffeine makes me jittery, tired and dizzy (quite the unpleasant combination).  The Gaia supplement does the same thing to me.  For those who care about taste, this supplement has a definite "herbal" flavor.  It's not pleasant, but it's not horrible or bitter (at least, not to me).For those who are not sensitive to caffeine, this is a quality supplement with lots of high-quality herbs.  It comes in a dark (brown) glass bottle.  Anybody who knows much about herbs will know that dark glass is the best type of container to preserve the potency of herbs.  The herbs in this supplement are: Astragalus root, Schisandra berry, Korean Ginseng root, Green Tea leaf, Black Elderberry berries, American Ginseng root, Ginger root, Fresh Nettle seed, Nettle leaf.  The other ingredients are: water, organic honey and citric acid.If this hadn't caused such a caffeine-like reaction for me (probably from the green tea and ginseng), this would have been perfect for boosting my energy and immune system.  I believe it will be helpful for those who don't have such reactions.

title: Jarrow Formulas NattoMax, 100 mg, 30 Count
reviewText: Nattokinase is one of many enzymes isolated from the fermented food product known as Nattō (boiled soybeans fermented specifically with the bacteria Bacillus subtilis), and it is supposed to help with circulation (blood pressure and possibly clotting disorders).  Since I don't have a clotting disorder, I can't say whether or not it helps with that.  I can, however, state categorically that this didn't help at all with my blood pressure.For those who do find this formula effective, be aware that it is recommended that you stop taking it two weeks before surgery, due to its possible clot dissolving properties.
